==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pastry
<hw>Pas"try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pastries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The place
where pastry is made.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Articles of food made of paste, or having a crust
made of paste, as pies, tarts, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pastry cook</b></col>, <cd>one whose occupation is to
make pastry; <as>as, the <ex>pastry cook</ex> of a
hotel</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pasturable</ent>⟦br⟧
